   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty THERE IS NONE RIGHTEOUS Scripture: Rom 3:9-20 All are under sin Man is born in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Man grows up in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Man lives in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Man wallows in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>All men are under sin.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>There is none righteous A righteous man is just and faultless before God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Using just and faultless as a yardstick to measure a man, we find that there is none righteous, because man is not normal toward God and is not just toward man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>There is none that does good Righteousness is up to the standard of justice, but good is exceeding the standard of justice.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Whenever you do something more than what you ought to do, you are doing something that is good.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>For example, you hired a servant and promised to pay him 600 monthly.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>If you pay him only 580, you have done something unrighteous.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>If you give him 650, you have done something good.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>But even if you do something good, there is none that can do good out of a pure heart.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Most good works contain side effects which expose that the heart is not pure.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Consequently, there is none that does good, not even one.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The conditions of man There is none that understands.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>All are confused and foolish, not knowing how to behave themselves before God and before men.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>There is none that seeks God who is the source of righteousness, the origin of all good.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>There is none that seeks Him; therefore there is none righteous and none that does good.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>All have turned aside.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>All have together become useless.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Their throat is an open grave.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Everything that comes out of men is stinking and dead.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Their tongues work deceit.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The poison of asps is under their lips.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Their mouths are full of cursing and bitterness.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Their feet are swift to shed blood.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Ruin and misery are in their ways.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>They know not the way of peace.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>There is no fear of God before their eyes.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>After talking about these twelve points of man s condition, all will have to bow down their heads and confess that there is none righteous, none that does good, not even one.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The world is under the condemnation of God Man has sins, and God has the law.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>The sins of man conflict with the law of God.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>According to His law, God has to condemn man.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Since all have sinned, all are under God s condemnation.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>How can a man become righteous?</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Confess that you are not righteous, neither can you become righteous.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>In other words, admit that you have no righteousness, and that you can do nothing that is righteous.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Believe in the Lord Jesus, and receive Him as your righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Receive the Lord Jesus as your living Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>He makes you righteous and causes you to live out His righteousness.</S>
   </TEXT>
